WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
I saw the spark in their eyes when they were given something to lead and they believed in them so much

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.000
and I feel the power. I am sure that for these children, this will not be forgotten.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:18.000
This year we set out with the Mental Leader program in Mathematics

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:26.000
out of the understanding that success in mathematics does not rely only on knowledge but also on a sense of capability, perseverance, and personal excellence.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:32.000
17 teachers from seven schools in the city underwent a significant professional and mental process.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:40.000
They learned to look at learning in a different way, to identify the places where students get stuck or give up

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
and to turn those moments into a growth engine.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:54.000
Inside the classrooms, they implemented mental tools such as success tests, self-assessment, goal setting, and learning from mistakes.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:02.000
Through these tools, a new language began to be built – a language that speaks about effort, responsibility, and the belief in the ability to improve.

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:10.000
These conversations I would have with the students aren't just for nothing, and they aren't just something that is only a personal connection;

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:16.000
they really build a certain process and a certain independent learner.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:24.000
The very discourse, this language that stops, is already the elevation of the students, of the people for whom it is more difficult.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:32.000
The very fact that there is a language and they are told, 'Guys, it's not all going to be just grades and knowledge now,

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:40.000
but also the building of your character, learning from mistakes,' all these things we are going to learn together, how to get out of it. Not just from

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:48.000
learning that 2 plus 2 equals 4, but everything around it. And I think it gave and gives some effect both to me and to them.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:56.000
Truly students who arrived from a very low starting point, and even if they haven't yet reached the 'top'

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:04.000
like 70 or 80, you see that something in their self-confidence and motivation

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:12.000
is changing. That is to say, these are two things that seem parallel to us but are a bit different,

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:20.000
and as soon as a child has this place where their mental axis is strengthened,

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:28.000
and their motivation and the results of these 'fitness tests'

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:36.000
give them joy—it's not just confidence, but a confidence that is justified.

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Alongside the work in the classrooms, we created a citywide community that speaks the same language; it's very noticeable in the discourse and discussions.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:52.000
The teachers didn't just acquire tools; they began to think together, to refine together, and thus build an innovative educational perception

00:02:52.000 --> 00:03:00.000
of the mathematical mindset. One of the most exciting things that emerged from the process

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:08.000
is that the change didn't just occur among the students, but also among the teachers themselves.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:16.000
The teachers dared to take on new professional challenges—advancing to teaching for matriculation exams

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:24.000
at the highest levels, leading classes to impressive achievements, integrating innovative tools into their teaching,

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:32.000
even choosing to stay in the system out of a renewed sense of meaning. The teachers testified that they

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:40.000
themselves experienced professional mental development. They testified that belonging to the Mental Leader program

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:48.000
was for them a privilege, an anchor, and a source for personal development. And for me, this is the essence of the program:

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:56.000
to build within the city and within the schools a community of teachers who lead a real change—

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:04.000
one that starts with their professional identity, continues with their shared language and teaching practices,

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:12.000
and influences the way students learn, progress, and begin to believe in themselves